# Agent Instructions

Use indexed code intelligence before broad grep or guessing.

Project index manifest:

- `.agent-index/agent-index.yaml`

Project skills:

- `.agents/skills/agent-index-router`
- `.agents/skills/agent-index-workspace`
- `.agents/skills/agent-index-lifecycle`

Rules:

- Use project-level skills under `.agents/skills`.
- For initial workspace setup, use `.agents/skills/agent-index-workspace/scripts/initialize-workspace.ps1`.
- Do not run workspace manifest update and repo exclude maintenance in parallel.
- Use lifecycle skills for setup, refresh, validation, repair, and provider changes.
- Use usage skills for daily retrieval and analysis.
- For cleanup of repo-local index artifacts, use `.agents/skills/agent-index-workspace/scripts/clean-project-index.ps1`; pass `-StopProjectMcp` only when intentionally stopping this project's MCP process tree.
- After stopping project MCP processes, restart the Codex session before MCP tool verification.
- Do not run bare `gitnexus` or bare `npx gitnexus`; use project wrappers under `.agent-index/bin`.
- Do not create repo-local `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, or `.claude/skills/...` from GitNexus.
- Project workspace/lifecycle scripts maintain child repo `.git/info/exclude` entries for local index directories such as `.codegraph/`, `.gitnexus/`, and `.understand-anything/`.

